      <hedline>
        <hl1>THE MARKETS: CURRENCIES</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Japanese yen drops on speculation that business confidence survey will not prompt Japanese central bank to raise interest rates; in New York, dollar settles at 108.84 yen, up from 108.02; graph; chart (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>THE YEN FALLS. The yen dropped on speculation that a business confidence survey would not prompt the Japanese central bank to raise interest rates. In New York, the dollar settled at 108.84 yen, up from 108.02 on Friday.</p>
      </block>
